CenterFan:
Caps are triangulated by placing a vertex in the center and creating a fan to the boundary. This works well if the path is convex,
but can create invalid geometry if it is concave.
Delaunay: Caps are triangulated to maximize the minimal angle in the triangles using Delaunay triangulation.
EarClipping: Caps are triangulated using a standard ear clipping approach. This could result in some very thin triangles.
